# Test strategy — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

What to test, at which layer, for each change. Tests live under `{{TEST_DIR}}/`.

## Layers

| Layer | Tests | Covers |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Unit | use cases, value objects, pure logic | every decision-table row for that logic |
| Repository / data | repository impls against a real/fake store | contract methods + each Failure |
| Integration / UI | flows across layers, screens | primary flow + empty/loading/error states |

## Bug-CLASS gate map

Fix the bug CLASS, not the instance: push prevention to the lowest layer, add the
cheapest gate that covers the whole class.

| Bug class | Prevent (lowest layer) | Detect (gate) |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Wrong data / count / sort | repository contract | unit test on the read model |
| Behavior / navigation | use case + state contract | interaction test per decision row |
| Validation slips | value-object invariant | unit test per rule |
| Visual / layout (UI) | shared widget + tokens | golden / snapshot test |
| Boundary / error mapping | error contract | failure-path test |
<!-- FILL: add project-specific classes -->

## Per-change requirement
- New testable branch → a decision-table row + its test (no exceptions).
- A bug fix → a regression test that fails before the fix.
- Map every test back to a decision-table ID or a contract method.
